ll,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fail"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lose heart, to despair"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to foil, to thwart, to frustrate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"failure","examples":[{"text":"لفت السياسي نديم الجابري اليوم الجمعة الى ان الخلافات واضحة في التحالف الشيعي ابرزها عملية تسجيل التحالفات لخوض الانتخابات المقبلة ، معتبرا انه لا توجد رؤية مشتركة لمكونات التحالف الوطني بشأن القضايا الوطنية والانشقاقات في الكتل السياسية ناتجة عن فشلها الذريع.","english":"The politician nadīm al-jabrī has on Friday drawn attention to the patent disagreements in the Shia alliance, most notably the alliances for the campaign for the election of the coming year, judging that there is no common vision about the constituents of the national alliance over the national affairs and the splits in the political blocs arising from their abject failure."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"disappointment, letdown, flop, dud, fiasco"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَشِلَ (fašila) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"failed, unsuccessful, futile, vain, fruitless"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"faint-hearted, cowardly, craven, chicken"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null}